# Session Execution Policy

Use the user-selected session by default. The local runtime is opt-in for implementation work.

## PRIORITY: User Session Choice (applies first)

**When the user types "claude", "codex", "cursor", or asks to open them**—help them open that app/session. Do NOT call `run_local_pipeline`. Do NOT invoke `bash ./Local`.

- "claude", "open claude", "start claude" → help open Claude (app, claude.ai, or Claude CLI)
- "codex", "open codex", "start codex" → help open Codex
- "cursor", "open cursor", "cursor session" → help open Cursor (new window, Composer, etc.)

**Never route session-open requests to local agent.** Codex, Claude, and Cursor are independent; the local agent (Local, local-codex) is opt-in only when the user explicitly says "local", "local agent", "Local", "local-codex", "Ollama", etc.

## MANDATORY Agent Behavior (for implementation tasks only)

- If the user is already in a Codex, Claude, or Cursor session and asks for implementation work there, execute the work in-session end to end.
- Do not stop at a generated command or ask the user to run the local runtime manually when the current session can perform the task.
- Route implementation to the local runtime only when the user explicitly asks for Local, local-codex, local agent, or Ollama.
- If a local-runtime workflow is chosen, invoke it directly rather than telling the user to do it.

## Do NOT Use (for implementation)

- Unrequested local-runtime handoffs
- Manual "run this yourself" responses when the current session can act
- Any external model APIs or rate-limited APIs when a local-runtime path was explicitly chosen

## Chat Cost (Cursor)

To minimize cost when using Cursor chat: use **Cursor Settings > Models > Add local model (Ollama)** and prefer local models in the model picker. This keeps chat usage local and near-zero cost.

## Local Runtime Entrypoints

- `bash ./Local` — interactive CLI; use `/pipeline <task>` or plain text
- `scripts/run_pipeline.sh "<task>"` — batch pipeline (auto-review at end)
- `scripts/local_team_run.py "<task>" <target_repo>` — low-level

**Review always runs at the end** of each pipeline run.
